responded: I need to understand how the document can be freed during the execution. Let me check if there are any reference counting issues. The problem seems to be that `docp` is accessed after the document has been freed. 

Looking at the stack trace more carefully:
1. The document is freed in `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref_directly` 
2. But then `docp->encoding` is accessed at line 1649

The issue is that `docp` is a pointer to the xmlDoc that gets freed, but the code continues to use it. The solution is to cache the encoding value before any operations that might free the document.

Let me create a patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 9650d090290..ff01e0ec779 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1618,6 +1618,7 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry

 	libxml_doc_props const* doc_props = dom_get_doc_props_read_only(intern->document);
 	bool format = doc_props->formatoutput;
+	const char *encoding = (const char *) docp->encoding;

 	zend_string *res;
 	if (nodep != NULL) {
@@ -1632,7 +1633,7 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry
 		 * w.r.t. the implicit return in DOM_GET_OBJ). */
 		old_xml_save_no_empty_tags = xmlSaveNoEmptyTags;
 		xmlSaveNoEmptyTags = (options & LIBXML_SAVE_NOEMPTYTAG) ? 1 : 0;
-		res = intern->document->handlers->dump_node_to_str(docp, node, format, (const char *) docp->encoding);
+		res = intern->document->handlers->dump_node_to_str(docp, node, format, encoding);
 		xmlSaveNoEmptyTags = old_xml_save_no_empty_tags;
 	} else {
 		int converted_options = XML_SAVE_AS_XML;
@@ -1646,7 +1647,7 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry
 		/* Save libxml2 global, override its value, and restore after saving. */
 		old_xml_save_no_empty_tags = xmlSaveNoEmptyTags;
 		xmlSaveNoEmptyTags = (options & LIBXML_SAVE_NOEMPTYTAG) ? 1 : 0;
-		res = intern->document->handlers->dump_doc_to_str(docp, converted_options, (const char *) docp->encoding);
+		res = intern->document->handlers->dump_doc_to_str(docp, converted_options, encoding);
 		xmlSaveNoEmptyTags = old_xml_save_no_empty_tags;
 	}

