responded: I see the same pattern here - `docp->encoding` is accessed in line 1590. The issue seems to be that the document can be freed between getting the document pointer and accessing its fields.

Let me now create a fix. The solution is to cache the encoding value right after retrieving the document pointer to avoid accessing potentially freed memory later:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 9650d090290..b646260c0b6 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1606,6 +1606,7 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry
 	zval *nodep = NULL;
 	xmlDoc *docp;
 	xmlNode *node;
+	const char *encoding;
 	dom_object *intern, *nodeobj;
 	int old_xml_save_no_empty_tags;
